# Platform Extensions & Spinoff Ideas

> Revenue opportunities that extend or leverage existing ventures (LazyGolf, Rent-a-Nerd, ndev).

---

## Philosophy

**Build on What Exists:**
The best new venture ideas often come from extending something you're already building. These opportunities:
- Leverage existing code/infrastructure
- Target adjacent customer segments
- Create flywheel effects between ventures
- Lower risk than greenfield ideas

---

## LazyGolf Platform Extensions

### Extension 1: LazyGolf Pro (B2B Tier)

**Concept:** Enterprise/B2B version of LazyGolf for golf courses, clubs, and corporate clients.

#### Target Customers

| Customer Type | Use Case | Price Point |
|---------------|----------|-------------|
| Golf Courses | Manage member leagues, events | $199-499/mo |
| Corporate HR | Company golf leagues, outings | $149-299/mo |
| Golf Clubs | Multi-league management | $299-599/mo |
| Resorts | Guest tournament management | $399-799/mo |

#### Features Beyond Consumer

- White-label branding
- Custom domain support
- Advanced reporting/analytics
- Multi-admin access
- API access for integrations
- Dedicated support
- Tee time system integration
- Payment processing for entry fees

#### Revenue Model

| Tier | Price | Features |
|------|-------|----------|
| **Course Basic** | $199/mo | 3 leagues, 100 members, basic branding |
| **Course Pro** | $399/mo | 10 leagues, 500 members, full white-label |
| **Enterprise** | $799/mo | Unlimited, API, dedicated success manager |

#### Viability Assessment

| Factor | Assessment |
|--------|------------|
| Viability | High |
| Effort | Medium (extend existing platform) |
| Revenue | $50K-200K/yr at 20-100 B2B customers |
| Moat | First-mover + golf expertise |

