### Extension 3: LazyGolf Marketplace

**Concept:** Two-sided marketplace connecting golfers with services.

#### Marketplace Categories

| Category | Sellers | Commission |
|----------|---------|------------|
| Golf Instruction | Local pros, instructors | 10-15% |
| Club Fitting | Fitters, pro shops | 10% |
| Golf Travel | Trip organizers | 5-10% |
| Equipment (Used) | Golfers selling clubs | 5% + listing fee |
| Golf Photography | Course photographers | 15% |

#### Integration with Rent-a-Nerd

- Caddy services listed on marketplace
- Tech support for golf devices
- Cross-promotion to golf audience

#### Viability Assessment

| Factor | Assessment |
|--------|------------|
| Viability | Medium |
| Effort | High (marketplace = chicken/egg problem) |
| Revenue | $20K-100K/yr at scale |
| Moat | Network effects (hard to build, harder to leave) |

**Risk:** Marketplaces are notoriously hard to bootstrap. Consider starting with just one category.

